An ideal place to store global constants is under the initializer folder.
<% code = "class Constant
  def self.continents
    ['Europe', 'Asia', 'Australia', 'North America', 'South America', 'Africa', 'Antarctica']
  end

  def self.gender
    {:female => 'gal', :male => 'guy', :else => '*@#\$'}
  end
end" %>
<% cache Digest::SHA1.hexdigest(code) do %>
	<% code_content = highlight_code(:rb, code).html_safe %>
	<%= render 'code_section', :title => "/config/initializers/constants.rb", :content => code_content %>
<% end %>
Then the constants can be used as below.
<% code = "You are from \<%= select_tag 'continents', options_for_select(Constant.continents) %\>.
Your are \<%= select 'gender', 'person', Constant.gender %\>." %>
<% cache Digest::SHA1.hexdigest(code) do %>
	<% code_content = highlight_code(:erb, code).html_safe %>
	<%= render 'code_section', :title => "/app/views/miscellaneous/select.html.erb", :content => code_content %>
<% end %>
Please note every time you revise the global constants, you may have to restart with <code>rails s</code> to reload the changes.

